---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const lastUpdated = '13 June 2026';
---

<Base
  title="Studio / Provider Privacy Notice — Moose"
  description="How Blubby Pty Ltd (trading as Moose Club) collects, holds, uses and discloses personal information about people who interact with Moose on behalf of studios, venues, providers and other businesses, in accordance with the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) and the Australian Privacy Principles."
>
  <header class="legal-nav">
    <div class="container legal-nav__inner">
      <a href="/" class="legal-nav__brand" aria-label="Moose home">
        <img src="/brand/logo/moose-wordmark-twotone.svg" alt="Moose" class="legal-nav__logo" />
      </a>
      <a href="/" class="legal-nav__back">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="14" height="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M19 12H5M11 18l-6-6 6-6"/></svg>
        <span>Back to home</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main id="main" class="legal">
    <div class="container legal__inner">
      <p class="eyebrow eyebrow--ink">Moose Club</p>
      <h1 class="display-s legal__title">Studio / Provider Privacy Notice</h1>
      <p class="legal__meta">
        Blubby Pty Ltd ABN 11 690 645 106 trading as Moose Club<br />
        Last updated: {lastUpdated}
      </p>

      <div class="legal__body">
        <p>
          This Privacy Notice explains how Blubby Pty Ltd ABN 11 690 645 106 trading as Moose Club
          (<strong>Moose</strong>, <strong>we</strong>, <strong>us</strong> or <strong>our</strong>)
          collects, holds, uses and discloses personal information about people who interact with
          Moose on behalf of studios, venues, providers and other businesses.
        </p>
        <p>
          This Privacy Notice outlines how we collect, use, disclose and protect personal information
          in accordance with the Privacy Act 1988 (Cth) and the Australian Privacy Principles.
        </p>
        <p>
          This Privacy Notice applies to business-side users and contacts, including Participating
          Studios, Partner Studios, Other Feature Providers, studio owners, operators, managers,
          instructors, admin staff, other representatives and other people who use, administer or
          interact with Moose on behalf of a studio, venue, provider or business.
        </p>
        <p>
          If you use Moose personally as a Moose User, the Moose User Privacy Policy may also apply.
        </p>

        <h2>1. About Moose</h2>
        <p>
          Moose is a platform that enables fitness studios to form direct cross-venue access
          partnerships with other Participating Studios.
        </p>
        <p>
          Moose also enables studios, venues, providers and other businesses to make Other Features
          available through Moose from time to time.
        </p>
        <p>
          To operate Moose, we may collect and share information between Moose, Participating Studios,
          Partner Studios, Other Feature Providers, Moose Users, software providers, payment providers
          and other service providers.
        </p>

        <h2>2. What personal information we collect</h2>
        <p>The kinds of personal information we collect may include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>identity and work contact information, such as name, work email address, phone number, role, title, employer, studio, venue or business;</li>
          <li>information about owners, operators, managers, instructors, admin staff, authorised users and other representatives of a studio, venue, provider or business;</li>
          <li>Platform account information, including login details, account permissions, access levels, security settings and actions taken in the Platform;</li>
          <li>onboarding, sales, account management, support and business development communications;</li>
          <li>studio, venue, provider and business profile information, including locations, services, classes, schedules, facilities, operating details and commercial contact information;</li>
          <li>information connected with Partnerships, Partner Studios, Crossover Session availability, booking availability, attendance, usage, access settings, restrictions and Platform configuration;</li>
          <li>information connected with Other Feature Providers and Other Features;</li>
          <li>fees, payments, invoices, billing, reconciliation, revenue share, commercial allocation and transaction information;</li>
          <li>CRM, booking system, studio management system, payment system, integration, API, technical configuration, data mapping, error, log and troubleshooting information;</li>
          <li>analytics, reporting, benchmarking, usage, performance and operational information;</li>
          <li>complaint, incident, safety, conduct, access, suspension or dispute-related information where relevant to Moose, Moose Users, studios, venues, providers or business representatives;</li>
          <li>technical and device information, including IP address, device information, browser type, log data, cookies, analytics information and Platform usage information; and</li>
          <li>any other information you, a studio, a venue, a provider, a Moose User or another person provides to us in connection with Moose.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Some information may be sensitive information, including health, injury, incident or
          risk-related information if it is provided in connection with a Moose User, incident,
          complaint or safety matter. We will only collect sensitive information where permitted by
          law.
        </p>

        <h2>3. How we collect personal information</h2>
        <p>We may collect personal information:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>directly from you when you contact us, use the Platform, create an account, attend onboarding, request support, enter into commercial discussions or otherwise interact with Moose;</li>
          <li>from Participating Studios, Partner Studios, Other Feature Providers, Moose Users and other business representatives;</li>
          <li>through booking systems, CRM systems, studio management systems, payment systems, integrations, APIs and other systems used by studios, providers or Moose;</li>
          <li>from payment providers, billing providers, software providers, analytics providers, support tools and other service providers;</li>
          <li>automatically through the Platform, website, app, cookies, analytics tools and similar technologies; and</li>
          <li>from third parties where permitted by law or where reasonably required to operate Moose.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          If you provide personal information about another person, you must ensure you are authorised
          to do so and that the person is aware of this Privacy Notice.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Why we collect, use and disclose personal information</h2>
        <p>
          We collect, use and disclose personal information for purposes connected with operating
          Moose, including to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>onboard studios, venues, providers and other businesses to Moose;</li>
          <li>create, administer and manage Platform accounts, user access, permissions and security;</li>
          <li>manage relationships with Participating Studios, Partner Studios, Other Feature Providers and other business contacts;</li>
          <li>enable Participating Studios to make the Moose Upgrade available to their members;</li>
          <li>enable Partnerships, Partner Studio access, Crossover Sessions, bookings, availability, attendance and related Platform functionality;</li>
          <li>enable Other Feature Providers to make Other Features available through Moose;</li>
          <li>operate, maintain, test, improve and develop Moose and the Platform;</li>
          <li>configure, support, troubleshoot and maintain integrations, APIs, CRM systems, booking systems, studio management systems and other connected systems;</li>
          <li>process, support and reconcile fees, invoices, payments, refunds, revenue share, commercial allocations and other commercial arrangements;</li>
          <li>provide reporting, analytics, benchmarking, usage insights, performance insights and operational information;</li>
          <li>communicate about onboarding, product updates, new features, support, integrations, operations, payments, legal documents, Partnership opportunities, promotional opportunities, commercial offers, referral incentives, case studies and expansion opportunities;</li>
          <li>send marketing and business development communications to studio, venue, provider and business contacts;</li>
          <li>manage incidents, complaints, disputes, investigations, safety matters, conduct issues, insurance matters and legal claims;</li>
          <li>protect Moose, Moose Users, studios, venues, providers, business representatives, the Platform and the integrity of the Moose network;</li>
          <li>comply with laws, regulations, legal processes and regulatory requests;</li>
          <li>support a proposed or actual investment, financing, restructure, merger, acquisition, sale of shares, sale of business or assets, due diligence process or other corporate transaction; and</li>
          <li>for any other purpose disclosed to you or permitted by law.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Sharing personal information</h2>
        <p>We may disclose personal information to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Participating Studios, Partner Studios, Other Feature Providers and their authorised representatives;</li>
          <li>Moose Users where reasonably required to operate Moose, manage access, support bookings or provide relevant information about studios, venues, providers or services;</li>
          <li>payment processors, billing providers, software providers, hosting providers, analytics providers, CRM and booking system providers, communications providers and other service providers;</li>
          <li>professional advisers, insurers, auditors, financiers, investors, prospective investors, buyers, prospective buyers, related bodies corporate, transaction counterparties and business partners where reasonably required;</li>
          <li>government agencies, regulators, courts, tribunals, law enforcement or other parties where required or permitted by law;</li>
          <li>other parties involved in an incident, complaint, dispute, claim, investigation, safety matter or misconduct issue; and</li>
          <li>any other person with your consent or where otherwise permitted by law.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We only share business-side personal information to the extent reasonably required for
          Moose, including to administer accounts, manage commercial relationships, support
          integrations, operate the Platform, manage bookings and access, support safety and conduct,
          respond to incidents and provide business reporting.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Studio, provider and business systems</h2>
        <p>
          Moose may collect, use and disclose information through systems used by studios, venues,
          providers and Moose, including booking systems, CRM systems, studio management systems,
          payment systems, integrations, APIs and other software tools.
        </p>
        <p>
          This may include information required to configure, test, operate, troubleshoot, support or
          improve integrations, booking flows, availability syncing, reporting, reconciliation and
          Platform functionality.
        </p>
        <p>
          You are responsible for ensuring that any personal information you provide to Moose, or make
          available to Moose through a system or integration, is collected and disclosed to Moose
          lawfully.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Aggregated, anonymised and de-identified information</h2>
        <p>
          Moose may generate, use and disclose aggregated, anonymised or de-identified data and
          insights generated through Moose.
        </p>
        <p>
          This may include information about usage, demand, booking patterns, attendance, retention,
          studio performance, provider performance, category performance, geographic trends and
          Platform activity.
        </p>
        <p>
          Moose may use or disclose this information for analytics, benchmarking, reporting, product
          development, commercial analysis, investor reporting, marketing, improving Moose, supporting
          studios and providers, and other business purposes.
        </p>
        <p>
          Where we use or disclose aggregated, anonymised or de-identified information, we will take
          reasonable steps so that the information does not reasonably identify an individual.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Cookies, analytics and digital technologies</h2>
        <p>
          We may use cookies, pixels, software development kits, analytics tools and similar
          technologies to operate the Platform, remember preferences, understand usage, improve Moose,
          measure performance and support marketing or communications.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may be able to disable cookies through your browser settings, but some parts of Moose or
          the Platform may not work properly if you do so.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Marketing and business communications</h2>
        <p>
          We may use your contact details and Platform activity to send you marketing, product,
          business development and promotional communications about Moose, including product updates,
          new features, onboarding material, promotional opportunities, Partnership suggestions,
          commercial offers, case studies, referral incentives and expansion opportunities.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may opt out of marketing communications using the unsubscribe function or by contacting
          us.
        </p>
        <p>
          We may still send you non-marketing communications, including business, account, legal,
          operational, support, integration, payment and security communications.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Overseas disclosure</h2>
        <p>
          Some of our service providers, systems, hosting providers, analytics providers, payment
          providers, support providers or other third-party platforms may be located outside Australia
          or may store or process information outside Australia.
        </p>
        <p>
          The countries in which information may be stored or processed may change from time to time.
        </p>
        <p>
          Where required by law, we will take reasonable steps in relation to overseas disclosures of
          personal information.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Security and retention</h2>
        <p>
          We take reasonable steps to protect personal information from misuse, interference and loss,
          and from unauthorised access, modification or disclosure.
        </p>
        <p>
          We may store personal information electronically, including in cloud-based systems and
          third-party platforms.
        </p>
        <p>
          We retain personal information for as long as reasonably required for the purposes described
          in this Privacy Notice, or as required or permitted by law.
        </p>
        <p>
          When personal information is no longer required, we may delete, destroy, de-identify or
          anonymise it, subject to legal, operational, accounting, dispute and backup requirements.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Access and correction</h2>
        <p>
          You may request access to personal information we hold about you, or ask us to correct
          personal information that is inaccurate, out of date, incomplete, irrelevant or misleading.
        </p>
        <p>We may need to verify your identity before responding.</p>
        <p>
          We may refuse access or correction where permitted by law. If we refuse a request, we will
          explain why where required by law.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Complaints</h2>
        <p>If you have a privacy complaint, please contact us using the details below.</p>
        <p>We will consider your complaint and respond within a reasonable time.</p>
        <p>
          If you are not satisfied with our response, you may contact the Office of the Australian
          Information Commissioner or another relevant privacy regulator.
        </p>

        <h2>14. Changes to this Privacy Notice</h2>
        <p>We may update this Privacy Notice from time to time.</p>
        <p>
          If we make significant changes, we may notify you by posting the updated version on the
          Platform, by email, or by any other method we reasonably consider appropriate.
        </p>
        <p>
          The updated version will apply from the date it is published, made available or otherwise
          notified by Moose.
        </p>

        <h2>15. Contact us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions, requests or complaints about privacy, please contact:
        </p>
        <p class="legal__contact">
          Blubby Pty Ltd ABN 11 690 645 106 trading as Moose Club<br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@trainmoose.com">privacy@trainmoose.com</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="legal-foot">
    <div class="container legal-foot__inner">
      <span>© {new Date().getFullYear()} Moose Club. Made in Australia.</span>
      <a href="/">Return home</a>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Base>

<style>
  /* Slim header — section anchors don't exist on this route, so this page
     ships its own minimal nav instead of reusing MSNav. */
  .legal-nav {
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.86);
    backdrop-filter: blur(14px) saturate(140%);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(14px) saturate(140%);
    position: sticky;
    top: 0;
    z-index: 100;
  }
  .legal-nav__inner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    height: 72px;
  }
  .legal-nav__logo { display: block; height: 30px; width: auto; }
  .legal-nav__back {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    padding: 9px 14px;
    border-radius: var(--r-sm);
    transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease-out), background var(--dur-fast);
  }
  .legal-nav__back:hover { color: var(--ink); background: var(--navy-50); }

  .legal { padding-block: clamp(48px, 7vw, 88px); background: var(--paper); }
  .legal__inner { max-width: 760px; }
  .legal__title { color: var(--navy); margin-top: 18px; }
  .legal__meta {
    margin-top: 16px;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-mute);
  }

  .legal__body { margin-top: 40px; }
  .legal__body h2 {
    font-size: clamp(19px, 1.8vw, 24px);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--navy);
    margin-top: 44px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .legal__body p {
    font-size: 15.5px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .legal__body strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 700; }
  .legal__body ul {
    list-style: disc;
    padding-left: 22px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .legal__body li {
    font-size: 15.5px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .legal__body a {
    color: var(--pink);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .legal__contact { font-weight: 500; }

  .legal-foot {
    background: var(--navy-900);
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
    padding-block: 28px;
    font-size: 13px;
  }
  .legal-foot__inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .legal-foot a {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
    transition: color var(--dur-fast) var(--ease-out);
  }
  .legal-foot a:hover { color: #fff; }
</style>
